ems like native images might not support certain resources or classpath features. I need to ensure tests run in the native image by default and catch UnsupportedFeatureError only if dynamic class loading is truly needed. This means I want to avoid direct reflection and instead use ClassScanner for scanning. I'll need to consider metadata for nested test classes and ensure that resources are effectively reachable. I'll create necessary resource directories if they aren't present, aiming for coverage reports to confirm things work correctly. ClassScannerTest will be the new top-level public class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing Class Loading for cn_hutool.hutool_all**\\n\\nI need to consider if scanning the package \\\"cn_hutool.hutool_all\\\" would load multiple tests, which might lead to unwanted initializations. To play it safe, I’ll filter to accept only ClassScannerSubject classes. While it will load all .class files in that package, it's acceptable as long as no static initializations occur. If there are any, they'll likely be safe since they won’t initialize automatically. Alternatively, I might scan for an exact class name or use the constructor's package name as the full class name.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JavaClassPaths**\\n\\nI'm considering the issue with JavaClassPaths returning a failure message. It seems like it might not throw an Error if the assertion fails. I might need to catch the Error only instead. I'm wondering if I should avoid asserting if it’s native but also questioning if that’s a good idea since the native will run anyway. Maybe I should inspect the results from the native test further to understand what went wrong.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1tZt2h4M5BPi37ZEq3REnnBs|fc_01e5907865f501b10169f44145a2e08195b48bc1e6fbc2cfcf", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cn.hutool/hutool-all/5.8.25/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml", "limit": 200}}], "api"